  "prompt": "Do consulting firms show their consultants' transcripts to their clients?",
  "response": "Consulting firms typically do not share their consultants' transcripts with clients. The relationship between consulting firms and their clients is generally based on trust, reputation, and the expertise of the consultants, rather than their academic records. Clients are usually more interested in the consultants' professional experience, industry knowledge, track record, and the consulting firm's overall reputation.\n\nHowever, in some cases, clients might inquire about the background and qualifications of the consultants who will work on their projects. In these situations, the consulting firm might provide general information about the consultants' educational and professional backgrounds, but it is uncommon for them to share detailed academic transcripts. It's also important to consider privacy and confidentiality concerns, as sharing personal academic records could breach privacy agreements or policies.",
